{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A unit test of just the file-filter function can miss wiring bugs between PR changed-file input and analyzer dispatch. REAL-INFRA: No real network/OS behavior is required if changed-file metadata and repo files are provided locally. MOCK-HIDE: Pure mocks of both sides could hide path/normalization mismatches; integrating selector + scanner catches this.","test_description":"Run the pipeline components end-to-end in-process with a temp workspace containing changed and unchanged files plus a simulated PR changed-file list; assert only changed paths are passed to static-analysis execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Grouping can fail at module handoff (rule output -> aggregator -> comment formatter), which a single-function unit test may not catch. REAL-INFRA: Real GitHub API is not required to verify grouping correctness; capture the composed comment payload locally. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking formatter output directly would hide formatting/aggregation defects.","test_description":"Feed mixed-severity findings through the real aggregation and comment-rendering pipeline, using a local fake comment sink; assert output sections and counts are correctly grouped by error/warning/info.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: Timeout behavior depends on subprocess execution, filesystem throughput, and runner-like environment characteristics. MOCK-HIDE: In-process or mocked linter timing can pass while real subprocess invocation exceeds budget. This is a runtime/performance boundary beyond local module wiring.","test_description":"Execute the actual linter command path over a generated 200-file corpus in a CI-like runner/container, measure wall-clock end-to-end pipeline time (including invocation and aggregation), and fail if it exceeds a safety threshold below 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: Correctness depends on real subprocess crash semantics (exit code/signal/stdout-stderr truncation) and recovery control flow. MOCK-HIDE: Mocked crash responses often miss real process-failure edge cases, causing false confidence. No LLM dependency.","test_description":"Run the pipeline against a fixture set where one file triggers an actual linter crash in a child process; assert the orchestrator continues with remaining files, aggregates surviving findings, and emits a final PR-comment payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Real failures often come from cross-module key construction differences (rule id/path/line normalization) rather than dedup logic alone. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network needed; local wiring is sufficient. A pure unit test may miss parser-to-aggregator mismatch.","test_description":"Pass findings from multiple rule emitters through the real normalization + aggregation pipeline and assert only one output entry remains for duplicates sharing file, line, and message identity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
